<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">29</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">3</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">May 1 2009</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">721</span> - <span property="pageEnd">740</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19448112/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">19448112</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2009.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: May 1 2009</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.293085113">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=HAART+%3D+highly+active+antiretroviral+therapy&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">HAART = highly active antiretroviral therapy</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=HIV+%3D+human+immunodeficiency+virus&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">HIV = human immunodeficiency virus</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MIP+%3D+maximum+intensity+projection&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MIP = maximum intensity projection</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MPR+%3D+multiplanar+reformatted&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MPR = multiplanar reformatted</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=3D+%3D+three-dimensional&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">3D = three-dimensional</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=2D+%3D+two-dimensional&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">2D = two-dimensional</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=VR+%3D+volume-rendered&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">VR = volume-rendered</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Review of volume-rendered images from multidetector CT facilitates an understanding of normal anatomy of the small-bowel mesentery, which is difficult to fully appreciate from axial images alone, and helps characterize pathologic processes involving the region.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Pamela T.</span> <span property="familyName">Johnson</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Russell H. Morgan Department of Radiology and Radiologic Sciences, Johns Hopkins School of Medicine, 601 N Caroline St, Room 3140D, Baltimore, MD 21287. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received May 1, 2008; revision requested June 26 and received September 25; accepted October 1. E.K.F. receives research support from Siemens and General Electric Company and is a member of their advisory boards and a cofounder of HipGraphics; all other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Johnson/Pamela+T" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Karen M.</span> <span property="familyName">Horton</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Russell H. Morgan Department of Radiology and Radiologic Sciences, Johns Hopkins School of Medicine, 601 N Caroline St, Room 3140D, Baltimore, MD 21287. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received May 1, 2008; revision requested June 26 and received September 25; accepted October 1. E.K.F. receives research support from Siemens and General Electric Company and is a member of their advisory boards and a cofounder of HipGraphics; all other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Horton/Karen+M" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con3" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Elliot K.</span> <span property="familyName">Fishman</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Russell H. Morgan Department of Radiology and Radiologic Sciences, Johns Hopkins School of Medicine, 601 N Caroline St, Room 3140D, Baltimore, MD 21287. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received May 1, 2008; revision requested June 26 and received September 25; accepted October 1. E.K.F. receives research support from Siemens and General Electric Company and is a member of their advisory boards and a cofounder of HipGraphics; all other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Fishman/Elliot+K" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-authors-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="doc-footnote"><b>Address correspondence to</b> P.T.J. (e-mail: <i><a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#e0908a8f888e938fd5a08a888d89ce858495"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="f888929790968b97cdb892909591d69d9c8d">[email&#160;protected]</span></a></i>).</div></section></section></div><div id="core-collateral-metrics" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-timeline" aria-hidden="true"></i>Metrics &amp; Citations</h2></header><section id="tab-metrics-inner" role="tabpanel"><h3>Metrics</h3><section>



        
